verbs.description: denaturalize (third-person singular simple present denaturalizes, present participle denaturalizing, simple past and past participle denaturalized)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To revoke or deny the citizenship of.
examples: After the regime fell, the leader was executed and the prinicipal party members were denaturalized and deported.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To make less natural; to cause to deviate from its nature.
(transitive) To cease to treat as natural.
examples: One question these scenes pose for cultural theory is whether such depictions denaturalize rape and denormalize masculinist pleasure in viewing sexual violence.
